## When to use
Use this skill when you need to monitor and analyze disk I/O operations on your system for performance tuning or troubleshooting purposes.

## Approach
Utilize the `shell_exec` tool to run the 'iostat' command, which provides statistics about the system's input/output block devices. This approach is effective for gathering real-time data on disk activity.

## Example
To monitor disk I/O usage every 5 seconds, use the following KDEV shell_exec commands:
```bash
shell_exec("iostat -dx 5")
```

## Pitfalls
Ensure that 'iostat' is installed on your system. This command may not be available on all systems by default and might require installation of additional packages.